HEADWORD: Math
<hw>Math</hw> <pr>(m⟦acr⟧th)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>m⟦aemac⟧⟦edh⟧</ets>; akin to <ets>m⟦amac⟧wan</ets> to mow, G.
<ets>mahd</ets> math. See <er>Mow</er> to cut (grass).]</ety> <def>A
mowing, or that which is gathered by mowing; -- chiefly used in
composition; <as>as, an after<ex>math</ex></as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The first mowing thereof, for the king's use, is wont to be sooner
than the common <qex>math</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

